        Hello everyone!!!
        I haven't been here in months... Though for the new year, I thought I'd come back :)

        Incredibly overjoyed for RAYE taking the #1 spot with Escapism. Her career has been an extremely long journey, with lots of struggles with her label, who weren't allowing her to release an album and how this lead to her new start as an independent artist. She has been resilient, and worked very hard to get here. The song is somewhat of a masterpiece and showcases her strong writing skills and a boldness to try something unique and risky, in a musical climate that has been dominated by standards set for how music should sound by labels. Her new creative freedom since becoming independent, in my opinion, has allowed her to unlock a lot of held back potential, which is definitely shown in the other songs she has released. Hard Out Here, Black Mascara & The Thrill Is Gone all have me anticipating her upcoming album 'My 21st Century Blues', it's going to be good!!!
